────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

1. INTRODUCTION

Welcome to YouTube Tags Extractor ("the App", "we", "our"). This Privacy
Policy explains how the App handles information when you use it on your
Android device.

By using the App, you agree to this Privacy Policy. If you do not agree,
please do not use the App.


2. INFORMATION WE DO NOT COLLECT

We do not collect, store, transmit, or have access to:

- Your name, email address, phone number, or any contact information
- Your Google account or YouTube account credentials
- Your device's unique identifiers (IMEI, Android ID, GAID, etc.)
- Your location data (GPS, IP-based, or otherwise)
- Your browsing history or usage history within the App
- Camera, microphone, contacts, or file system data
- Analytics, crash reports, or behavioral data
- Cookies or tracking pixels


3. HOW THE APP WORKS

YouTube Tags Extractor works as follows:

1. You enter a YouTube video URL or video ID into the App.
2. The App makes an HTTPS request directly to www.youtube.com to retrieve
   the publicly available page for that video.
3. The App parses the response on your device to extract the keywords
   metadata embedded in every public YouTube video page.
4. The extracted tags are displayed on your screen.

Nothing is sent to any server other than YouTube.com. All processing
happens locally on your device. We do not operate any server, backend,
or database. We never see your requests.


4. INTERNET PERMISSION

The App requests the INTERNET permission solely to communicate with
www.youtube.com. This connection is:

- Made only when you tap "Extract Tags"
- Directed exclusively to YouTube.com — no other domain
- Used only to fetch publicly visible video metadata
- Encrypted via HTTPS at all times


5. THIRD-PARTY SERVICES

The App does not integrate any of the following:

- Advertising SDKs (AdMob, Facebook Audience Network, etc.)
- Analytics SDKs (Firebase, Mixpanel, Amplitude, etc.)
- Crash reporting tools (Crashlytics, Sentry, etc.)
- Social login (Google Sign-In, Facebook Login, etc.)
- Cloud databases or backend platforms

The only external service the App contacts is YouTube.com, operated by
Google LLC. Your interaction with YouTube.com is governed by Google's
Privacy Policy: https://policies.google.com/privacy


6. DATA SHARING

Since we collect no personal data, there is nothing to share, sell, or
disclose to any third party — and we never will.


7. DATA SECURITY

All network communication uses HTTPS (TLS encryption). No user data is
stored on-device beyond what Android itself caches temporarily for
network requests. The App does not create any local database or persistent
storage of personal information.


8. CHILDREN'S PRIVACY

YouTube Tags Extractor is rated Everyone on Google Play and is suitable
for all ages. Because we collect no personal information whatsoever, the
App inherently complies with the Children's Online Privacy Protection Act
(COPPA) and similar international regulations.

We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13
(or under 16 in the EU/EEA under GDPR). Since we collect no data at all,
this is guaranteed by the App's design.


9. YOUR RIGHTS (GDPR / CCPA)

If you are a resident of the European Union, United Kingdom, or
California, you have rights regarding your personal data under GDPR, UK
GDPR, and CCPA respectively.

Because we collect zero personal data, there is no data to access,
correct, delete, or port. Your privacy rights are fully respected by
default — there is simply no data to act on.


10. CHANGES TO THIS PRIVACY POLICY

We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Any changes will
be reflected with an updated "Last Updated" date at the top of this
document. Continued use of the App after changes are posted constitutes
your acceptance of the revised policy.

We will notify users of any material changes via the App's release notes
on Google Play.
